!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

unwilling /ʌnˈwɪlɪŋ/

1. ADJ If you are unwilling to do something, you do not want to do it and will not agree to do it. 不愿意的 

例： Initially the government was unwilling to accept the defeat. 最初，政府不愿意接受失败。 

2. unwillingness N-UNCOUNT 不愿意 

例： ...their unwillingness to accept responsibility for mistakes. …他们不愿意承担出错的责任。 

3. ADJ You can use unwilling to describe someone who does not really want to do the thing they are doing. 不情愿的 

例： A youthful teacher, he finds himself an unwilling participant in school politics. 作为一位青年教师，他发现自己很不情愿地卷入了学校的权术之争。 

4. unwillingly ADV 不情愿地 

例： He accepted his orders very unwillingly. 他非常不情愿地接受了他的命令。

</div>

